Kenya’s Main Teachers’ Union Calls Off Strike Over Staff, Nation Reports

-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 
2011-09-12T04:49:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/kenya-s-main-teachers-union-calls-off-strike-over-staff-nation-reports.html
The  Kenya  National Union of
Teachers called of its week-long strike after the government
agreed to hire 23,000 teachers on permanent and pensionable
terms, the  Daily Nation  reported.  A long-term strategy will also be developed to address the
shortage of teachers in Kenya, the Nairobi-based newspaper said,
citing David Okuta, secretary general of the labor union.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  